Two years ago I would've said this was my perfect music app, but it's progressively gotten worse and it's almost unusable now. It's really difficult to navigate to what you're looking for. For instance, if I only want to listen to a specific album, I can't first find the artist and then the album, instead I have to scroll through a list of dozens and dozens and dozens of albums from every artist in my library to find the one album I want. If I want to listen to offline music only, it won't let me even view playlists that have online music. Which sucks because songs come and go from Amazon Prime music all the time, and if one of them gets removed, I can't even view that playlist when I'm offline. It used to be that the playlist would open and would just skip the unavailable music. And, worst of all, if I want to possibly buy a song or an album, it can't be done within the Amazon Music app anymore. It doesn't even let me view the availability. It just opens the Amazon Shopping app, which my phone hates and just slogs along for 5 minutes trying to load. *And* one time I got trapped in a loop where I exited the Amazon Shopping app and tried to go back into Amazon Music, but the music app thought I was still trying to buy a song, and just re-opened the shopping app. Force close didn't work, I actually had to restart my phone. There also used to be a time where I could listen to Prime Music without ads. But now I get an ad for Music Unlimited when I open the app, plus there's a banner for Unlimited across the top, and now there's even audio ads when listening to songs. Utter garbage. I'm about to switch to something else.

Why is it so hard to find a good music app? I switched to Amazon Music about a year ago after Google, in their infinite wisdom, removed the Play Music app in favor of YouTube Music. I don't use a music subscription service. I don't want to use a subscription service. So I find it extremely annoying when this app is incessantly promoting Amazon's music subscription. Amazon - I didn't want to sign up the first 300 times you showed me the ad, you can stop asking. I am also faced with one extremely annoying bug. When I unplug my phone from my car, without fail, this app skips back to the beginning of the playlist. It would be nice if Amazon's developers would spend time fixing bugs like this instead of serving me more ads for their overpriced subscription service. Unfortunately, it seems to me like this is about as good as music apps get nowadays. Relative to other apps, Amazon Music is fine I suppose, but on an absolute scale, it's less than awesome.
